<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920127-0055</DOCNO><DOCID>920127-0055.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Kruger Inc.:   Newsprint Machine Is Closed   Until at Least End of Year</HL><DATE>01/27/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C17</SO><MS>BASIC MATERIALS (BSC)</MS><IN>RAW AND FINISHED PAPER PRODUCTS (PAP)</IN><RE>CANADA (CN)NORTH AMERICA (NME)</RE><LP>   Kruger Inc., Montreal, said it will close a newsprintmachine at its mill in Trois-Rivieres, Quebec, until at leastthe end of 1992, reducing newsprint production at thefacility by 45,000 metric tons this year.   A metric ton equals 2,204.62 pounds.</LP><TEXT>   The closely held pulp and paper concern also said itsCorner Brook, Newfoundland, mill will close a newsprintmachine Feb. 9 for at least one month, reducing the outputthere by at least 6,000 metric tons this year. The companyadded that short-term shutdowns at its mills inTrois-Rivieres and Bromptonville, Quebec, have reducednewsprint production by 5,000 metric tons since the beginningof the year.   Kruger said adverse market conditions will probably forceit to further reduce newsprint production during the year.</TEXT></DOC>